06:54.312 --> 06:56.735
- The Phantom?
- Unh, he keeps doing that.

06:56.940 --> 07:00.365
You know, overuse of smelling salts
can damage the nasal passages.

07:00.568 --> 07:01.615
- His or mine?
- His.

07:05.991 --> 07:08.414
The Phantom!

07:09.869 --> 07:11.496
Hey, I found that clipboard
the Phantom took.

07:11.705 --> 07:13.127
And also I quit.

07:13.331 --> 07:17.552
I ain't hanging around this place
for another second. It's haunted.

07:21.256 --> 07:23.099
“Christine must win"?

07:23.299 --> 07:27.304
Well, gang, it looks like we've got
another mystery on our hands.

07:33.101 --> 07:36.981
- Hold it right there.
- Hey, like, it's just a bass, man.

07:37.188 --> 07:38.986
Sure it is.

07:40.900 --> 07:46.157
- Oh, uh, well, go on in then.
- Thank you.

07:48.158 --> 07:51.913
Chrissy does not give interviews unless
she can approve all questions in advance.

07:52.120 --> 07:56.170
She will accept no questions regarding
politics, religion or her favorite color.

07:56.374 --> 07:57.546
Because I said so.

07:58.168 --> 08:01.547
- Well, hello there. Are you--?
- Are you trying to psych her out?

08:01.755 --> 08:04.634
- Is this some kind of mind game?
- I was just saying hi.

08:04.841 --> 08:07.560
- Well, don't.
- You can't just talk to Chrissy.

08:07.761 --> 08:10.514
She's very sensitive.
You have to talk to her...

08:10.722 --> 08:14.101
...before you talk to her to let her
know you're going to talk to her.

08:14.309 --> 08:16.311
- Isn't that right, sweetie?
- Whatever.

08:16.770 --> 08:17.817
You see?

08:19.939 --> 08:22.738
- Yeah, hi. We're here to check in.
- We're checking in!

08:22.942 --> 08:25.195
Uh, Mr. Ottoman's kind of
unconscious right now?

08:25.403 --> 08:28.282
- Are you saying we can't check in?
- They're saying we can't check in.

08:28.490 --> 08:30.584
- This is totally unacceptable.
- Uh...

08:30.742 --> 08:31.959
She said, "Uh."

08:32.159 --> 08:34.162
They're pretty much
like that all the time.

08:34.370 --> 08:38.796
- Hey, heh. You're Emma, right? The Violinist?
- Yeah. And you're Fred and Daphne.

08:39.000 --> 08:41.344
I saw your audition tape,
you guys were great.

08:41.544 --> 08:43.342
And I'm not just saying
that because of the cameras.

08:43.546 --> 08:45.640
- What cameras?
- Those cameras.

08:45.840 --> 08:48.263
You know, they're catching
all the backstage drama.

08:51.513 --> 08:55.643
That's the best part of the show.
All the who likes who, who hates who stuff.

08:55.850 --> 08:58.273
Hello, everyone,
and welcome to Talent Star.

08:58.478 --> 09:00.151
Hey, I'm your host,
Brick Pimiento.

09:00.355 --> 09:04.155
I just wanted to reassure you all that
everything is fantastic, just fantastic.

09:04.359 --> 09:07.078
There isn't a problem, nothing happened
and there's definitely no ghost.

09:07.278 --> 09:09.372
- Ghost?
- Ghost? I didn't say ghost.

09:09.572 --> 09:12.621
Why would I say ghost
when there's no ghost, heh? Fantastic.

09:14.369 --> 09:17.714
- There he is.
- Yeah, there he is.

09:18.623 --> 09:20.796
You're okay there,
right, Dewey, heh?

09:21.000 --> 09:24.254
Fantastic. Well, carry on.

09:30.969 --> 09:33.438
I smell dog.

09:35.682 --> 09:37.150
Uh, Mr. Ottoman,
are you all right?

09:37.350 --> 09:40.354
Dogs are nothing but big furry sacks
of germs. Did you know that?

09:40.562 --> 09:42.815
- I don't think that--
- I'm going to find that dog...

09:43.022 --> 09:46.071
...if it takes me all night.
Give me that.

09:47.694 --> 09:51.244
Mr. Pimiento. Mr. Pimiento!

09:51.447 --> 09:56.078
Can we have two minutes of your time?
We've got an act that's just terrific.

09:56.286 --> 09:57.458
Yeah, terrific.

09:57.662 --> 10:02.338
My friends, I've built my career
on two deeply held beliefs.

10:02.542 --> 10:06.388
One, all talent deserves
a chance to be seen.

10:06.588 --> 10:09.137
And two, juggling stinks.

10:12.177 --> 10:13.975
So, what have you got for me?

10:26.565 --> 10:28.533
Terrible. That was just...

10:31.653 --> 10:35.032
Aah! I don't know what that was
but I'm running away from it.

10:35.240 --> 10:36.708
Me too.

10:41.788 --> 10:42.835
Is it him?

10:45.876 --> 10:47.503
- Yeah, it's the Phantom.
- The Phantom?

10:47.711 --> 10:50.260
- What are they doing--?
- There.

10:50.464 --> 10:52.933
Now he's there.

10:53.133 --> 10:55.682
Velma, you watch the monitors.
You can tell me where he is.

10:55.886 --> 10:57.934
- Daphne, you come with--
- Yes.

11:07.439 --> 11:10.568
<i>- Which way?
- Turn left at the end of the hall.</i>

11:10.776 --> 11:12.073
Second door on your left.

11:12.277 --> 11:15.247
- Are you getting all this on camera?
- Yeah, this is great stuff.

11:15.447 --> 11:19.998
Fantastic. Should we use it for
promos or leak it to Whotube?

11:20.202 --> 11:22.921
- Both.
- Hmm.

11:44.726 --> 11:46.694
Look out!

11:49.189 --> 11:51.112
Are you okay?

11:52.859 --> 11:54.827
- Velma, which way?
- I don't know.

11:55.028 --> 11:56.450
I can't see where he went.

11:58.031 --> 12:00.125
In here.

12:04.538 --> 12:07.382
- He'll never think to look in here, right?
- Right.

12:08.750 --> 12:10.172
I smell lemons.

12:11.545 --> 12:13.673
Yeah, I smell lemons too.

12:13.880 --> 12:16.133
Do you smell lemons?

12:20.429 --> 12:21.726
There.
He's heading north.

12:21.930 --> 12:24.399
<i>- North, which way is that?
- Go left.</i>

12:24.599 --> 12:25.851
<i>No, right.
Then left.</i>

12:27.686 --> 12:29.359
- I'm sorry.
- No, I'm sorry.

12:29.563 --> 12:31.816
- I didn't mean to...
- Go.

12:32.024 --> 12:34.026
He's on the stairs.

12:37.654 --> 12:39.873
What?
Did you see that?

12:40.449 --> 12:43.373
Maybe he really is a ghost.

12:46.747 --> 12:48.294
How could he just disappear?

12:48.498 --> 12:51.468
- There must be a rational explanation.
- Yeah, like he's a ghost.

12:52.836 --> 12:55.965
A ghost who smells like lemons?
That sounds kind of weird.

12:56.173 --> 12:59.302
And it's not weird to have a ghost
who doesn't smell like lemons?

12:59.509 --> 13:01.056
We have to get to
the bottom of this.

13:04.139 --> 13:05.766
Dog.

13:07.225 --> 13:08.568
Dog, where?

13:08.769 --> 13:12.069
Get that germ sack out of here.
Right now.

13:12.272 --> 13:14.616
Did he leave footprints?
I think I see footprints.

13:14.816 --> 13:16.534
He didn't touch any walls, did he?

13:16.735 --> 13:21.206
Oh, my gosh. Now I'll have to sanitize
the entire building.

13:21.406 --> 13:23.374
Good thing I brought bleach.

13:23.575 --> 13:25.703
Out, I said. Out, out, out.

13:25.911 --> 13:27.379
Come on, guys.

13:27.579 --> 13:31.004
I want this floor buffed.
And I want it polished.

13:32.584 --> 13:35.713
Okay, I'll check us in to the hotel
and do some Internet research.

13:35.879 --> 13:38.507
Shaggy and Scooby,
you go to the library on State Street...

13:38.715 --> 13:40.968
...and see what you can find out
about the Opera House's history.

13:41.176 --> 13:43.270
How are we the choice
for library research?

13:43.470 --> 13:46.314
I'll see what I can find out in the building.
Daphne, you come with--

13:46.515 --> 13:48.392
Yes.

13:48.767 --> 13:50.986
- I'm going with Fred, heh.
- Ah.

14:04.866 --> 14:07.995
Welcome to the Hotel Canard.
How may I be of service?

14:08.203 --> 14:11.707
- Hello, I need to check--
- Hi, checking in. Barb and Lance Damon.

14:11.915 --> 14:15.715
- And Chrissy.
- I'm sorry, this young lady was--

14:15.919 --> 14:19.298
- Hey, are you giving us attitude?
- I think he's giving us attitude.

14:19.506 --> 14:23.636
Listen, buddy, I want someone
to take Chrissy's bags to the room now.

14:25.846 --> 14:26.972
Go ahead, I'll wait.

14:27.889 --> 14:28.981
Humph.

14:30.642 --> 14:32.394
Oh, Chrissy.
Are you okay?

14:32.602 --> 14:35.572
Of course, I'm okay.
Why wouldn't I be okay?

14:35.772 --> 14:38.525
Weren't you scared of the Phantom?
You were screaming--

14:40.152 --> 14:42.280
That wasn't a scared
scream, stupid.

14:42.487 --> 14:45.991
It was a happy scream because he told me
I'm gonna win the competition.

14:46.199 --> 14:47.917
- He told you--
- I'm gonna win.

14:48.118 --> 14:50.997
Even if he has to obliterate
all the other contestants.

14:51.163 --> 14:53.507
- Isn't that awesome? Heh.
Uh--

14:53.665 --> 14:56.885
It's true. We have a genuine psycho
on our side. Score.

14:57.085 --> 15:00.510
And that's why the Phantom wrote,
“Christine must win" on that clipboard.

15:00.714 --> 15:02.808
- Her name's Christine.
- But call her Chrissy.

15:03.008 --> 15:05.761
Only don't call her Chrissy
because don't talk to her.

15:05.969 --> 15:09.599
- You're getting nerd breath all over her.
- Come on, Chrissy. Keep smiling.

15:12.225 --> 15:14.944
- Oh, they're unbearable, aren't they?
- Yeah.

15:15.145 --> 15:19.992
- Who are you?
- I am The Great Pauldini.

15:21.067 --> 15:22.944
- My card.
- Uh, that's an egg.

15:25.113 --> 15:29.038
Okay, egg, card, whatever.
I made it appear, right?

15:29.242 --> 15:33.372
Can you do that? No, you can't
because you're not a magician, heh.

15:33.580 --> 15:35.332
- Who's a magician?
- You are?

15:35.540 --> 15:37.884
Oh, yeah, heh. Up high.

15:38.084 --> 15:40.633
That's what I'm talking about.

15:40.837 --> 15:44.341
- He's pretty unbearable himself.
- Tell me about... Hello?

15:47.427 --> 15:49.304
Waldo. The ventriloquist.

15:49.513 --> 15:52.016
And here's Hufnagel,
my dummy.

15:52.224 --> 15:55.353
- Hiya, toots.
- And I sit on his lap.

15:55.560 --> 15:58.359
It's funny. Not at all demeaning.
Right?

15:58.563 --> 16:01.191
- Right.
- Right. Catch you later.

16:02.067 --> 16:04.365
Oh, my gosh, he is adorable.

16:04.569 --> 16:08.449
I am not adorable. I am hot.

16:08.657 --> 16:11.752
- You know, what? He kind of is.
- Totally.

16:11.952 --> 16:13.044
Um, I saw him first.

16:13.245 --> 16:15.964
- Hey, you guys are that band, right?
- Yes.

16:16.164 --> 16:19.168
We are Girlasaurus Rex.

16:22.337 --> 16:24.214
Oh, my gosh, we are so metal, heh.

16:24.422 --> 16:28.268
Cathy. It's so not metal to say,
“Oh, my gosh, we're so metal."

16:28.468 --> 16:29.811
Right. Sorry.

16:30.011 --> 16:32.184
We were a country act
until three months ago.

16:32.389 --> 16:34.483
We agreed we weren't
telling people that.

16:34.683 --> 16:37.607
Now, come on, look surly.

16:39.980 --> 16:44.952
I think a lemon-scented ghost
would fit right in with this crowd.

16:50.824 --> 16:54.169
Fred, why do ghosts and monsters
and stuff turn up wherever we go?

16:54.369 --> 16:56.918
- Is it something about us?
- No, this happens to everyone.

16:57.122 --> 16:59.295
- What?
- It would be too much of a coincidence...

16:59.499 --> 17:00.546
...if this only happened to us.

17:00.750 --> 17:04.095
So logically everyone must run
into ghosts and monsters all the time.

17:04.296 --> 17:06.219
- Really?
- Sure, it's simple math.

17:06.423 --> 17:07.925
They must be everywhere.

17:15.265 --> 17:17.939
- What are you doing here?
- What are you doing here?

17:18.101 --> 17:21.901
I'm Mel Richmond. I own this building
and I have a right to lurk in it.

17:23.440 --> 17:26.284
- You must be from the show, right?
- Yeah, we're contestants.

17:26.483 --> 17:30.034
Right. Well, uh, good luck to you.
You make a cute couple.

17:30.238 --> 17:32.661
We're not a cute couple.
I mean, heh, we're not a couple...

17:32.866 --> 17:35.995
...so we can't be a cute one, although
we would be if we were. Which we're not.

17:37.370 --> 17:41.170
I mean, it's not that we don't like each
other, we just don't "like" like each other.

17:41.374 --> 17:44.799
It's not likely. Right, Fred?
Or do we?

17:45.003 --> 17:47.973
We don't, right? Do we?
Why are we talking about this so much?

17:48.173 --> 17:51.222
Can we change the subject now, please?
This is none of your business.

17:51.384 --> 17:53.933
Uh, Mr. Richmond, do you know
anything about the Phantom?

17:54.095 --> 17:58.225
Argh, that business again.
Look, that was all way before my time.

17:58.433 --> 18:02.563
I inherited this place a few years ago
when my father passed away.

18:02.771 --> 18:04.192
Oh, I'm so sorry.

18:04.396 --> 18:07.070
Me too, it's costing me thousands
of dollars a week.

18:07.274 --> 18:08.617
I can't do anything with it.

18:08.817 --> 18:13.163
People are still spooked by that Phantom
nonsense and that was 35 years ago.

18:13.364 --> 18:14.707
What was 35 years ago?

18:14.865 --> 18:18.165
Uh, it happened back in the '70s.

18:18.744 --> 18:23.671
<i>Before that there had been some oddities.
But, you know, nothing scary.</i>

18:23.874 --> 18:28.004
<i>But when my father turned the place
into a disco, all heck broke loose.</i>

18:28.212 --> 18:32.513
<i>The Phantom wreaked havoc every night.
People thought it was part of the show.</i>

18:36.804 --> 18:39.182
<i>Despite the Phantom,
the club flourished.</i>

18:39.390 --> 18:41.484
<i>Customers looked
forward to seeing him.</i>

18:41.684 --> 18:45.530
<i>Even though it was said his mask
hid a terrible deformity.</i>

18:48.941 --> 18:50.659
<i>No one was ever really hurt.</i>

18:50.859 --> 18:54.614
<i>But then the Phantom became
more destructive.</i>

18:55.906 --> 18:58.455
<i>He even set fires.</i>

18:59.326 --> 19:04.628
<i>Then one night.
He destroyed the disco ball.</i>

19:08.961 --> 19:11.134
<i>After that,
no one came back.</i>

19:11.672 --> 19:14.050
<i>Finally, my father had to close
the place down.</i>

19:15.634 --> 19:19.605
I hadn't been able to rent it at all until
the Talent Star people came around.

19:19.805 --> 19:22.103
Now they say the Phantom's back.

19:22.307 --> 19:25.436
Well, maybe I'll get lucky
and he'll burn the place down...

19:25.644 --> 19:27.863
...so I can collect the
insurance money, eh? Heh, heh.

19:28.063 --> 19:32.534
Or maybe I should put on a cape and mask
and do it myself, ha, ha.

19:35.237 --> 19:38.081
What? Ah, now,
don't look at me like that.

19:38.282 --> 19:41.877
You see, that's why
I don't make jokes.

19:51.378 --> 19:54.006
Know what I like best
about going to the library, Scoob?

19:54.173 --> 19:55.595
- The books?
- Nope.

19:55.758 --> 19:58.477
The fact that it's far, far away
from that Phantom guy.

19:58.677 --> 19:59.894
You said it.

20:00.095 --> 20:04.566
And it's nice that Velma trusts us
with such an important assignment like--

20:09.396 --> 20:10.864
Pizza.

20:17.112 --> 20:18.204
Give me eat.

20:18.405 --> 20:20.954
Right this way, sir.

20:27.581 --> 20:30.960
Do you have anything bigger
than the extra-extra-large?

20:31.168 --> 20:32.715
Yeah, but it's not on the menu.

20:32.920 --> 20:37.050
Oh, and you have to sign a release
saying we're not responsible if you die.

20:37.257 --> 20:38.884
- We'll take it.
- All righty.

20:39.051 --> 20:41.099
But I'll have to move you
to another table.

20:41.303 --> 20:42.350
Why?

20:42.554 --> 20:44.556
Because this one
is smaller than your pizza.

20:44.765 --> 20:47.188
Awesome.

21:07.746 --> 21:10.340
Aah! Mm!

21:24.513 --> 21:27.983
If you don't mind,
we'd like to be alone with the pizza.

21:28.183 --> 21:29.480
Okey-dokey.

21:29.643 --> 21:31.896
Uh, we can wrap up the
leftovers for you.

21:32.104 --> 21:34.323
Leftovers?

22:07.806 --> 22:11.527
I'd just like to say that it's
an honor to be in your presence.

22:11.727 --> 22:13.775
Like, I'm sure it is.

22:26.116 --> 22:29.871
I love you, Lotte.
Lotte! I love you.

22:31.872 --> 22:33.249
Thank you.

22:35.959 --> 22:37.836
- Who's that?
- That's Lotte.

22:38.045 --> 22:41.515
She's on Talent Star, and she's already
won a bunch of other talent shows.

22:41.715 --> 22:45.015
<i>She was great on
America's Got Singing...</i>

22:45.218 --> 22:49.268
<i>...and Sing or Die
and Singetty-Sing-Song-Sing.</i>

22:57.064 --> 22:58.111
Mm-mm.

22:58.273 --> 23:03.951
I do not sign for anyone wearing
tights and shorts. Because it's wrong.

23:06.823 --> 23:09.667
Yeah, yeah, you better run.

23:11.244 --> 23:13.246
Leave us.

23:18.919 --> 23:22.298
I want you to take a message
to Daphne and Fred.

23:22.506 --> 23:27.637
Tell them they don't stand a chance.
I will crush all who oppose me.

23:27.844 --> 23:29.938
I will feast upon their blood.

23:30.138 --> 23:34.018
Their families will weep
over their smoldering corpses.

23:34.226 --> 23:37.651
I will leave nothing
but their scarves.

23:37.854 --> 23:40.073
So swears Lotte.

23:40.273 --> 23:44.824
L-O-T-T...

23:47.990 --> 23:49.287
...E!

23:49.491 --> 23:50.663
Lotte.

23:57.040 --> 23:58.917
Keep the change.

24:11.263 --> 24:12.810
- Hey, guys.
- Where have you been?

24:13.015 --> 24:15.564
- The library closed hours ago.
- The what?

24:16.393 --> 24:18.862
Never mind, I found plenty
of information online.

24:19.062 --> 24:21.406
There was definitely
a Phantom back in the '70s.

24:21.606 --> 24:23.950
I don't think the one we saw
was the same person.

24:24.151 --> 24:26.028
This is from earlier tonight.

24:26.236 --> 24:29.240
- Where did you get that picture?
- It's all over the Internet.

24:29.448 --> 24:31.871
Talent Starts really milking this
for publicity.

24:32.826 --> 24:35.670
See?
The outfit is different.

24:35.871 --> 24:40.092
What we saw today was someone taking
advantage of the old stories for their own.

24:40.292 --> 24:43.341
But you saw him disappear, right?
He must be a real ghost.

24:43.545 --> 24:46.424
I saw it on a monitor.
it could have been faked.

24:46.631 --> 24:49.851
- So who are the likely suspects?
- Definitely Chrissy's parents.

24:50.052 --> 24:51.099
You're right.

24:51.303 --> 24:54.352
The Phantom seems interested in making
sure Chrissy wins the competition.

24:54.556 --> 24:56.058
And Brick Pimiento.

24:56.266 --> 24:59.566
He was a little too quick to capitalize
on the Phantom for publicity.

24:59.770 --> 25:02.694
Could he be doing this
to boost the show's ratings?

25:02.898 --> 25:05.651
What about Mel Richmond,
the guy who owns the Opera house?

25:07.527 --> 25:09.575
Maybe what he said
about insurance money wasn't a joke.

25:09.780 --> 25:12.283
What about Dewey Ottoman?
He's creepy.

25:12.491 --> 25:14.914
- Does he have a motive?
- Isn't creepy a motive?

25:20.040 --> 25:22.668
Ooh, ooh!
You gotta put Lotte down.

25:22.876 --> 25:24.423
You think Lotte
is the Phantom?

25:24.628 --> 25:28.178
I think she's scarier
than the Phantom, heh. Put her down.

25:30.884 --> 25:34.764
Hmm. Everyone on this list but Mel
Richmond and Lotte have been seen...

25:34.971 --> 25:36.894
...at the same time
as the Phantom.

25:39.184 --> 25:40.310
Guys, it's getting late.

25:40.519 --> 25:42.066
We have the dress rehearsal
in the morning...

25:42.270 --> 25:44.022
...and the big show
tomorrow night.

25:44.231 --> 25:46.073
I say we get some sleep.

25:47.399 --> 25:50.073
Sure thing,
Mr. Jones.

25:52.154 --> 25:53.827
I will break you.

25:57.618 --> 26:02.374
We have adjoining rooms, Shaggy.
You can go this way.

26:04.750 --> 26:05.876
See you in the morning.

26:07.419 --> 26:08.796
He said he'll see me.

26:09.547 --> 26:11.049
- Hmm.
- Ugh.

26:16.554 --> 26:17.771
Huh?

26:22.810 --> 26:24.653
Daph?

26:32.695 --> 26:34.697
- Trouble sleeping?
- Ah, yeah.

26:34.905 --> 26:37.875
- Are you okay? What's wrong?
- I'm fine.

26:38.075 --> 26:41.670
You're obviously not fine, Daphne.
Why don't you tell me about it?

26:41.871 --> 26:45.796
I'm in love with Fred.
There, I said it.

26:47.084 --> 26:49.507
Really?
Wow, I never would have...

26:49.712 --> 26:51.464
Gosh, that's a shocker.

26:51.672 --> 26:55.393
I've kept it a secret for so long.
I just had to tell someone.

26:55.593 --> 26:58.813
Shouldn't you be telling someone else?
Like, maybe Fred?

26:59.013 --> 27:01.391
Oh, no.
Oh, my gosh, no.

27:01.599 --> 27:04.148
I was hoping this competition
would bring us closer...

27:04.351 --> 27:07.525
...but even after all the time
rehearsing and performing together...

27:07.730 --> 27:09.323
...I just can't say anything.

27:09.857 --> 27:12.531
I even wrote a song,
to that tune Fred composed.

27:12.735 --> 27:14.282
It explains how I feel about him.

27:14.486 --> 27:17.660
But if I think about singing it
I feel like I'm going to throw up...

27:17.865 --> 27:20.618
...or pass out or both.

27:21.035 --> 27:22.332
You have to tell him, Daph.

27:22.536 --> 27:24.664
You'll never know how he feels
unless you talk to him.

27:24.872 --> 27:28.672
I can't. Maybe if I win Talent Star,
that would give me the confidence.

27:28.876 --> 27:30.503
Maybe then I could talk to him.

27:31.128 --> 27:34.803
Velma, we have to win.
We just have to.

27:55.027 --> 27:58.497
Scooby-doo, you awake?
I can't sleep.

27:58.697 --> 28:00.699
Me neither.

28:00.908 --> 28:02.535
You want the bed?

28:02.743 --> 28:07.499
No. It's been almost two hours since we
had that pizza and I'm starving, heh.

28:07.706 --> 28:10.209
Maybe the hotel has
a vending machine or something.

29:01.635 --> 29:02.932
Dog!

29:05.264 --> 29:07.358
I touched a dog.

29:07.558 --> 29:10.311
I have dog bacteria.

29:28.662 --> 29:31.916
- Like, take it easy there, Phantom dude.
- Yeah.

29:36.795 --> 29:40.425
That's not taking it easy.
That's taking it very, very hard.

30:44.488 --> 30:45.535
It's been cut.

30:45.739 --> 30:50.165
It's okay, everyone. He's gone. No harm
done. Heh, everybody back to bed.

30:50.369 --> 30:51.416
Fantastic.

30:51.620 --> 30:54.169
This Phantom's gonna
get us a 40 share.

30:55.707 --> 30:58.176
Enough with the screaming.

30:58.377 --> 31:03.975
Gonna skin you alive. Good night.

31:05.384 --> 31:08.103
- Hey, no lemons.
- Yeah, you're right.

31:12.558 --> 31:15.061
A little baking soda
and water will get that out.

31:15.269 --> 31:17.738
- I'm sure the hotel staff will--
- No, no, no, please.

31:17.938 --> 31:20.487
I should get 45 minutes
of scrubbing out of this.

31:20.691 --> 31:23.444
That smoke bomb seemed like
something a magician would do...

31:23.652 --> 31:25.575
...and The Great Pauldini's
nowhere to be seen.

31:25.779 --> 31:27.406
True.
But does he have a motive?

31:27.614 --> 31:30.333
This just keeps
getting more and more mysterious.

31:30.534 --> 31:32.332
You know what the
real mystery is?

31:32.536 --> 31:35.540
How did you get hold of a net so fast
in the middle of the night?

31:35.747 --> 31:39.172
- Um, well, I...
- You sleep with a net, don't you?

31:39.376 --> 31:41.925
Lots of people do.

31:56.226 --> 31:58.320
Aw, look at the little...

31:59.146 --> 32:02.320
- ... baby?
- Gooby-gooby-goo

32:09.948 --> 32:11.621
Okay, people.

32:11.825 --> 32:14.749
We've only got one dress rehearsal,
so let's get it right.

32:14.953 --> 32:17.672
Chrissy Damon,
you're up first.

32:24.421 --> 32:26.344
- Chrissy.
- Ready.

