Was that your new act?
What are you, the human cannonball?

38:27.032 --> 38:28.909
No, we thought you
were the Phantom.

38:29.118 --> 38:32.213
What? Why would you think that?
That's crazy.

38:33.664 --> 38:34.711
Ah.

38:37.418 --> 38:38.715
The Great Pauldini.

38:53.726 --> 38:55.194
Still no sign of the Phantom.

38:55.394 --> 38:57.021
Maybe the whole thing's over.

38:57.229 --> 38:58.947
Waldo and Hufnagel?

39:00.232 --> 39:03.327
Say, Hufnagel,
are you an actor or a dummy?

39:03.527 --> 39:06.280
I don't know,
what's the difference?

39:07.072 --> 39:09.245
He's so hot.

39:09.450 --> 39:11.794
- Aah, oh, my gosh, he's on fire.
- Totally.

39:11.994 --> 39:14.213
No, I mean he's really on fire.

39:14.413 --> 39:18.463
Hey, Hufnagel, do you...?
Smell something burning?

39:18.667 --> 39:20.635
Aah, ugh!

39:25.382 --> 39:28.010
Christine must win!

39:28.218 --> 39:32.394
Security, find that Phantom.
Find him, find him!

39:33.891 --> 39:36.110
Waldo? Hey, you're not leaving,
are you, buddy?

39:36.310 --> 39:41.441
No, heh, I thought I'd stay and risk
my life for a stupid talent show.

39:41.649 --> 39:43.367
Hey, that's fanta--
Hey.

39:43.567 --> 39:45.569
Of course I'm leaving.

39:45.778 --> 39:49.282
And the rest of you will too,
if you have any sense.

39:49.657 --> 39:51.659
Ahem, my card.

39:51.867 --> 39:52.914
Give it to me.

39:53.118 --> 39:55.166
Come on, give it to me.

39:56.622 --> 39:58.545
Girlasaurus Rex!

39:58.749 --> 39:59.796
You're on.

40:01.961 --> 40:04.931
- We are...
- Girlasaurus Rex!

40:08.884 --> 40:13.310
One, two, one, two, three, four!

40:26.235 --> 40:29.990
Uh, strum, strum, twang!

40:37.913 --> 40:40.416
Christine must win.

40:43.127 --> 40:46.848
K.T.? Where is he?
Where is he?

40:47.047 --> 40:49.345
He's in the prop room.
He's in the coffee...

40:49.550 --> 40:53.430
He's everywhere.
What the heck?

40:53.929 --> 40:55.772
Don't worry. We'll find him.
Let's split up.

40:57.224 --> 40:58.396
Okay. The other way.

41:00.894 --> 41:05.240
Find him.
Now, now, now, now.

41:05.441 --> 41:06.818
Right, we're out of here.

41:07.026 --> 41:08.744
Heh, ladies, where are you going?
Come on.

41:08.944 --> 41:12.573
Dude, someone busted our instruments.
What's next, our heads?

41:12.780 --> 41:15.499
- Think we can catch up with Waldo?
- What do you mean, "we"?

41:15.658 --> 41:18.081
- Come back here.
- We've gotta do something.

41:18.244 --> 41:20.121
- Velma, you've seen all the acts, right?
- Yeah.

41:20.329 --> 41:23.003
Who you think the frontrunners are?
I mean, of the ones that are left?

41:23.207 --> 41:26.256
Honestly? You guys,
the violin girl and Chrissy.

41:26.461 --> 41:30.591
So if the Phantom wants Chrissy to win,
he'll try to get rid of Emma and us.

41:30.798 --> 41:33.768
Velma, can you get Emma's parents
to take her someplace safe?

41:33.968 --> 41:34.403
Sure.

41:34.429 --> 41:36.166
We're gonna set a
trap for the Phantom.

41:36.345 --> 41:38.018
And Daphne and I will be the bait.

41:38.222 --> 41:41.692
Oh, heh, good.
I mean, yeah, whatever.

41:44.437 --> 41:47.316
Well, uh, we're gonna
take a nap now.

41:47.523 --> 41:49.366
In our dressing room.

41:49.525 --> 41:51.243
Um, no one cares?

41:51.444 --> 41:56.041
Yeah, so, uh, we'll be asleep and napping.
Just totally unprotected.

41:56.240 --> 41:59.915
- In our dressing room. Asleep.
- Unguarded.

42:00.119 --> 42:03.589
- In our dressing room.
- Unguarded.

42:08.544 --> 42:12.594
- Hang tight. Something's bound to happen.
- To you, right? Not to us?

42:12.799 --> 42:14.267
What? I'm just asking.

42:14.467 --> 42:16.185
Hey, it's a fair question.

42:18.888 --> 42:21.437
Just a matter of time now.

42:41.994 --> 42:45.294
This is ridiculous.
We've been waiting forever.

42:45.498 --> 42:48.593
And, Velma, would you get
your elbow out of my ribs?

42:48.793 --> 42:51.672
I'm over here, Shaggy.

42:52.964 --> 42:54.637
Then whose big elbow...?

42:59.053 --> 43:00.145
What is it?

43:02.140 --> 43:03.266
Phantom!

43:10.189 --> 43:12.442
He must have gone through there.

43:12.650 --> 43:15.494
Like, I hate hidden passages.

43:15.695 --> 43:18.665
They never lead anywhere good.

43:28.916 --> 43:33.797
When's the last time we were in a hidden
passage and it led to, like, miniature golf?

43:39.760 --> 43:42.934
We're in the sewer
below the Opera House.

44:10.791 --> 44:14.841
Like, these sewers have so many
passageways, how are we gonna find--?

44:15.004 --> 44:16.426
Shh!

44:30.311 --> 44:31.904
Rats!

44:59.548 --> 45:00.765
Huh?

45:03.719 --> 45:05.972
Aah! Bats!

45:27.660 --> 45:30.755
Good thing this sweater
is a cable-knit.

45:34.417 --> 45:35.669
There it is again.

45:45.469 --> 45:47.437
This way.

46:14.498 --> 46:16.125
- Ha!
- Yipe!

46:16.292 --> 46:19.296
I suppose it was only
a matter of time until someone found me.

46:19.503 --> 46:22.052
Welcome to my home.

46:22.256 --> 46:26.352
I have lived here in the dank,
reeking sewers all my life...

46:26.552 --> 46:28.225
...forced to hide from society...

46:28.429 --> 46:32.775
...to conceal the hideous,
twisted mass of flesh that is my face.

46:32.975 --> 46:36.570
But now, I can hide no longer.

46:36.771 --> 46:41.368
Behold,
the Phantom of the Opera!

46:46.405 --> 46:48.282
Um, you look fine.

46:49.116 --> 46:50.959
I what?

46:51.160 --> 46:54.209
I mean, you're no Brad Pitt
or anything, but you're okay.

46:57.708 --> 47:03.260
But look. Gaze upon my foul,
deformed visage. I'm hideous. Hideous.

47:04.840 --> 47:07.263
Dude,
this is a funhouse mirror.

47:07.468 --> 47:10.722
It is? But this is the only mirror
I've ever looked in.

47:10.930 --> 47:15.310
I mean, I don't have any others, and
when I go out I always wear the mask.

47:16.352 --> 47:19.652
Hey, I look good.

47:20.356 --> 47:21.858
Well, this is embarrassing.

47:22.024 --> 47:23.401
Wow, uh, ehh!

47:23.567 --> 47:25.535
I wish I had the last 40 years back.

47:25.694 --> 47:28.322
Uh, so it's super
awkward right now.

47:28.531 --> 47:29.828
I, uh... Anyway, yeah.

47:30.032 --> 47:32.501
- Mr. Phantom--
- Steve. Steve Trilby.

47:32.660 --> 47:35.914
Uh, Steve. Why have you been
sabotaging the talent show?

47:36.622 --> 47:37.669
The what now?

47:37.873 --> 47:39.250
<i>Talent Star?
The TV show?</i>

47:39.458 --> 47:42.132
You wrecked instruments
and set fire to a dummy, and--

47:42.336 --> 47:45.180
Not me. I haven't been up at all lately,
except to get food.

47:45.381 --> 47:47.349
Is that why you were
in our dressing room?

47:47.550 --> 47:49.928
That's the secret door
to the vending machines.

47:50.136 --> 47:52.605
I like those burritos.
The bean and cheese ones?

47:52.805 --> 47:54.352
But back in the '70s...

47:54.557 --> 47:56.605
Oh, yeah. I mean,
I did some stuff back then.

47:56.809 --> 47:57.856
Stuff I'm not proud of.

47:58.060 --> 48:00.529
It was when they turned
the Opera House into a disco.

48:00.729 --> 48:02.527
I had loved the opera so much.

48:02.731 --> 48:04.529
I can hear everything
from down here.

48:04.733 --> 48:06.986
But that disco music
made me crazy.

48:07.194 --> 48:09.697
And those ridiculous outfits
the people wore.

48:09.905 --> 48:13.409
You know, the little neck scarf thingies
and the mini-skirts and...

48:14.326 --> 48:17.751
Oh!
But on you guys they work.

48:17.955 --> 48:20.128
Anyway, that was when
I was young and impetuous.

48:20.332 --> 48:23.506
I haven't bothered anyone
for almost 40 years now.

48:23.711 --> 48:26.931
Could I, um, see that mirror again?

48:29.049 --> 48:32.178
Look at me. I'm an Adonis.

48:32.386 --> 48:34.684
Guys, I'm pretty sure
he's telling the truth.

48:34.889 --> 48:37.608
But if he isn't behind everything
that's going on, then who...?

48:53.448 --> 48:55.041
Huh?

48:55.200 --> 48:56.292
Hello!

48:56.493 --> 48:58.461
Uh, kind of stuck up here.

48:58.620 --> 49:00.213
Oh!

49:00.872 --> 49:04.001
So could someone get a ladder,
or something?

49:04.209 --> 49:05.711
What happened?

49:05.877 --> 49:07.925
The harness is part
of my disappearing trick.

49:08.087 --> 49:11.091
I was working on it when the Phantom
shoved me off that catwalk.

49:11.299 --> 49:13.347
Hey, what's that up there?

49:13.551 --> 49:15.474
Oh, no, it's the Phantom.

49:18.723 --> 49:20.600
I'm going after him.
Watch the exits.

49:20.808 --> 49:23.357
- We'll put out the fire.
- Yeah.

49:40.453 --> 49:42.080
Come on, work.

49:43.581 --> 49:44.924
Thanks, Scoo-- Whoa!

49:47.418 --> 49:50.171
Like, double thanks.

49:57.053 --> 49:58.100
- Aah!
- Ow.

49:58.263 --> 49:59.731
You're squeezing my arm.

50:13.611 --> 50:15.363
- Aah!
- Look out!

50:15.530 --> 50:17.203
Ow. Quit it.

50:48.980 --> 50:51.358
Mel Richmond?

50:52.650 --> 50:55.028
I think I'm dying.

50:55.194 --> 50:57.242
Um, actually I'm pretty
sure you're okay.

50:57.447 --> 51:00.075
But look, I'm all bloody.

51:00.658 --> 51:04.333
There's some red paint on the... Do you
understand how mirrors work at all?

51:04.537 --> 51:07.290
Give me a break,
I grew up in a sewer.

51:12.086 --> 51:14.930
So you were gonna burn the place down
for the insurance money?

51:15.131 --> 51:17.304
Yes. And I would have
gotten away with it too...

51:17.508 --> 51:20.933
...if it hadn't been for you
meddling kids and your nosy dog.

51:21.137 --> 51:22.184
Dog? Where?

51:22.388 --> 51:24.061
- Zoinks!
- Uh-oh!

51:25.475 --> 51:26.772
Get back here.

51:30.104 --> 51:31.151
Relax, Richmond.

51:31.356 --> 51:37.580
- Is this the guy?
- That's him, officer. Mel Richmond.

51:38.404 --> 51:40.327
Wait.
This still doesn't make sense.

51:40.531 --> 51:44.001
If you wanted the insurance money,
why didn't you just burn the place down?

51:44.202 --> 51:45.829
- Why all the other stuff?
- I didn't.

51:46.037 --> 51:49.132
But whoever did gave me the idea
to put on this costume.

51:49.332 --> 51:51.300
Stupidest idea I ever had.

51:54.337 --> 51:57.591
- Christine must win!
- What the heck?

51:57.799 --> 52:02.430
Otherwise, I will rain death
and destruction down upon this place!

52:02.637 --> 52:05.356
So swears the Phantom!

52:08.726 --> 52:10.319
Now will you take this seriously?

52:10.520 --> 52:14.616
I want as many officers as you can
spare here for the show tonight.

52:14.816 --> 52:16.568
I was thinking the same thing buddy.
We're on it.

52:16.776 --> 52:19.120
So you'll do it?
You'll put all your men on this?

52:19.320 --> 52:21.243
And can you keep
that dog out of here too?

52:21.447 --> 52:24.951
Hello!
I still need a ladder!

52:25.159 --> 52:31.462
Hello!
The Great Pauldini is not pleased!

52:34.168 --> 52:35.465
Stop that dog.

52:51.728 --> 52:55.778
Well, well, guess they got away
because they're not here.

52:56.733 --> 52:59.452
Anywhere and aha!

53:03.614 --> 53:05.537
Darn it.

53:14.500 --> 53:16.093
- Brick!
- Aah!

53:17.628 --> 53:19.847
I wasn't doing anything.
I was just in there. Not doing anything.

53:20.047 --> 53:21.890
I was doing something
but it was nothing.

53:22.091 --> 53:24.890
Like, we have a totally
great act for you.

53:25.094 --> 53:26.562
Oh. Oh! Uh...

53:26.721 --> 53:30.146
Well, fantastic.
By all means, proceed.

53:31.601 --> 53:35.401
Say, Scooby-doo,
what bone will a dog never eat?

53:35.605 --> 53:39.075
I don't know, Shaggy.
What bone will a dog never eat?

53:39.609 --> 53:41.407
A trombone.

53:43.821 --> 53:48.372
- Heh, yeah, that's fan... Security.
- Aah!

53:48.534 --> 53:51.413
Scoob, what vegetable do you get
when you cross a dog with a rose?

53:51.621 --> 53:53.544
- I don't know, Shaggy.
- A collie-flower.

53:55.291 --> 53:56.417
Dog!

54:00.546 --> 54:02.844
- Mr. Pimiento?
- Blake and Jones.

54:03.049 --> 54:05.427
- Well, you must be happy.
- Why?

54:05.635 --> 54:09.105
Your odds of winning are way up.
Because there are only four acts left.

54:09.305 --> 54:11.603
Three.
The Great Pauldini just quit.

54:11.808 --> 54:16.985
Heh, whatever. Anyway, the publicity the
Phantom has generated has been fantastic.

54:17.188 --> 54:19.111
We're expecting our
highest ratings ever.

54:21.567 --> 54:23.911
Come on,
let me show you the projections.

54:24.111 --> 54:25.533
The sound room, huh?

54:31.828 --> 54:32.875
Still on.

54:37.542 --> 54:39.135
Hmm?

54:41.212 --> 54:45.592
So this would be heard
on the stage. Interesting.

54:46.175 --> 54:48.348
Do you keep the footage
all the cameras in here shoot?

54:48.553 --> 54:51.602
Well, of course. There's a whole
digital database on the server.

54:51.806 --> 54:53.274
- Could I look through it?
- Sure.

54:53.474 --> 54:55.442
But there's 2000 hours
of footage in there.

54:55.643 --> 55:00.740
Oh, man. Now there's no way I'm gonna
have time to go see the soap diamond.

55:12.577 --> 55:14.295
<i>Talent Star was starting
to get old...</i>

55:14.495 --> 55:18.500
...but this Phantom thing
has really spiced it up.

55:18.708 --> 55:22.133
If the Phantom shows up
we might really see someone get hurt.

55:22.336 --> 55:24.885
Oh, I hope.
I hope, heh.

55:26.924 --> 55:29.268
There's a lot of police
at the Opera House, Scooby.

55:29.468 --> 55:32.847
So if we're gonna get in,
this disguise has gotta be a good one.

55:34.056 --> 55:36.024
And voila.

55:36.225 --> 55:38.944
Perfect. Like, I think
this is gonna work, Scooby-doo.

55:39.145 --> 55:41.614
- Yeah.
- Now repeat after me.

55:41.814 --> 55:45.864
- These kids today...
- These kids today...

55:46.068 --> 55:51.199
...darn newfangled contraptions.
- ...darn newfangled contraptions.

55:51.407 --> 55:55.037
Excuse me, sonny. Does this
computer have an Internet in it?

55:55.244 --> 55:59.044
Excuse me, sonny. Does this
computer have an Internet in it?

55:59.248 --> 56:01.751
By George, I think he's got it.

56:05.963 --> 56:08.216
Ladies and gentlemen,
welcome to the Talent Star finals.

56:08.424 --> 56:11.394
I'm your host, the man, Brick Pimiento.

56:12.845 --> 56:15.644
Now, I'm sure you've all heard
that we've had some trouble.

56:18.809 --> 56:21.153
Mm-hm, terrible business.
Terrible.

56:21.354 --> 56:24.824
Because of this so-called Phantom,
we're down to just three acts.

56:25.024 --> 56:26.446
<i>Emma...</i>

56:26.651 --> 56:28.369
...Blake and Jones...

56:28.569 --> 56:30.697
...and Chrissy.

56:30.905 --> 56:32.828
Fantastic, ha, ha.

56:33.032 --> 56:38.128
By the end of the show tonight, one will
be crowned this year's Talent Star.

56:38.328 --> 56:40.205
The others will receive
a year's supply of Fudge-a-Roni.

56:40.413 --> 56:42.757
Fudge-a-Roni, the great taste of fudge
with the convenience of roni.

56:42.916 --> 56:44.133
Ooh!

56:46.252 --> 56:49.381
As you know, on Talent Star,
you decide the winner.

56:49.589 --> 56:51.057
You can vote by text or online.

56:51.257 --> 56:54.852
Your votes will be tallied in real time
and displayed on this scoreboard.

56:55.011 --> 57:01.235
Heh, and now, going out live
all over the world, I give you Chrissy!

57:03.812 --> 57:10.821
<font color="#00ffff">♫</font> <font color="#00ff00" face="Times New Romance">Stay away from my man, home-wrecker</font> <font color="#00ffff">♫</font>

57:11.736 --> 57:18.540
<font color="#00ffff">♫</font> <font color="#00ff00" face="Times New Romance">Nobody comes between me and my man</font> <font color="#00ffff">♫</font>

57:18.743 --> 57:20.461
<font color="#00ffff">♫</font> <font color="#00ff00" face="Times New Romance">Stay away</font> <font color="#00ffff">♫</font>

57:32.465 --> 57:33.557
- Got you.
- Aah.

57:34.968 --> 57:37.767
You were right, Emma,
you do make better bait than us.

57:48.398 --> 57:49.524
Lance Damon?

57:52.777 --> 57:54.779
So it was you all along?

57:54.988 --> 57:56.205
- When it wasn't Mel.
- Ugh.

57:56.406 --> 57:59.876
I would have gotten away with it if it
hadn't been for you meddling kids...

58:00.076 --> 58:02.625
...and your nosy old guy?

58:03.913 --> 58:06.541
Thanks, we'll take it from here.

58:06.750 --> 58:10.220
Blake and Jones.
You're on in 30 seconds.

58:10.795 --> 58:14.140
Brick. Blake and Jones have been cued.
They'll be on in 30.

58:16.259 --> 58:19.809
These darn newfangled kids.

58:20.013 --> 58:24.018
Ugh, your grandfather
smells like a dog.

58:25.393 --> 58:27.236
Yeah?
Well, you smell like lemons.

58:27.437 --> 58:30.441
It's the hand sanitizer.

58:31.232 --> 58:32.404
- Lemons.
- Lemons.

58:32.609 --> 58:34.327
Like the Phantom.

58:40.784 --> 58:44.379
Ugh, one side, doofus.
I killed out there.

58:44.579 --> 58:47.298
Heh, yeah,
fantastic.

58:47.499 --> 58:50.469
Uh, by the way, they just arrested
your dad, ciao.

58:51.419 --> 58:53.763
- Ugh.
- Sweetheart, daddy's in trouble.

58:53.963 --> 58:56.716
I told that pinhead
to watch his step. Idiots.

58:56.925 --> 59:00.646
Fantastic, Chrissy, just fantastic.
Wow, look at those numbers.

59:00.845 --> 59:03.098
Up next, Blake and Jones.

59:10.063 --> 59:14.569
