Sunshine after the rain</font></b></font> <font color="#ff0080">♫</font>

59:14.776 --> 59:18.997
<font color="#ff0080">♫ </font><font color="#00ffff"><b><font face="Curlz MT">Clouds rise up from the water
Nature's endless chain</font></b></font> <font color="#ff0080">♫</font>

59:19.197 --> 59:23.668
<font color="#ff0080">♫ </font><font color="#00ffff"><b><font face="Curlz MT">The world keeps on spinning
From day into the night</font></b></font> <font color="#ff0080">♫</font>

59:23.868 --> 59:28.169
<font color="#ff0080">♫ </font><font color="#00ffff"><b><font face="Curlz MT">From season to season
From darkness to light</font></b></font> <font color="#ff0080">♫</font>

59:28.373 --> 59:29.795
Where's Dewey?

59:29.999 --> 59:31.922
I don't know.
He's supposed to be here?

59:32.127 --> 59:34.221
- Where the heck is Dewey?
- Like, nobody knows.

59:34.379 --> 59:36.848
Well, wherever he is,
he's still wearing his headset.

59:37.048 --> 59:40.348
I can hear him. He's breathing hard.
Sounds like he's running and muttering.

59:40.552 --> 59:44.147
Something about soap. But that's what
he's always talking about so...

59:44.347 --> 59:46.224
- Mind if I borrow this? Thanks.
- Hey.

59:46.432 --> 59:50.187
Hey, you, yes. Get me another earpiece.
And a latte. Yeah, yeah, fantastic.

59:50.395 --> 59:54.195
Come on, Scoob.
We've got to get to Dewey's office.

59:57.193 --> 01:00:00.037
- Soap.
- Yeah. That's what he's talking about.

01:00:00.238 --> 01:00:03.833
The soap diamond.
It's right around the corner.

01:00:04.033 --> 01:00:06.161
What the heck are you guys
doing in here?

01:00:06.369 --> 01:00:08.667
Guys. Wait till you see
this footage I found of--

01:00:08.872 --> 01:00:12.672
No time. Dewey. Phantom.
Soap diamond.

01:00:15.545 --> 01:00:17.092
Dewey's the Phantom too.

01:00:17.297 --> 01:00:20.016
He told the police to assign
everyone they have here.

01:00:20.216 --> 01:00:23.766
He must have done that so no one would
be watching the mineralogical society.

01:00:23.970 --> 01:00:26.189
This way.

01:00:28.600 --> 01:00:30.398
Knock them dead, Emma.

01:00:31.436 --> 01:00:32.562
Is he saying anything?

01:00:33.563 --> 01:00:36.567
Oh, I can hear traffic.
He's outside.

01:00:36.774 --> 01:00:40.495
Like, he just said "Got it."
We might be too late.

01:00:45.450 --> 01:00:46.576
There.

01:00:48.536 --> 01:00:50.163
Dewey!

01:00:50.330 --> 01:00:51.752
Uh...

01:00:54.542 --> 01:00:58.342
I am the Phantom.
I know nothing of this Dewey.

01:00:58.546 --> 01:01:02.722
Dude, we know it's you.
You're still wearing your headset.

01:01:02.884 --> 01:01:04.306
Huh?

01:01:05.762 --> 01:01:07.764
Oh, darn.

01:01:17.732 --> 01:01:19.609
The soap diamond.

01:01:23.154 --> 01:01:25.248
No!

01:01:26.824 --> 01:01:28.747
Way to go, Scooby-doo.

01:01:30.119 --> 01:01:31.336
Uh-oh!

01:01:34.499 --> 01:01:36.797
I want that diamond!

01:01:57.897 --> 01:01:59.399
Ha!

01:02:04.404 --> 01:02:06.327
To the Mystery Machine.

01:02:38.313 --> 01:02:42.989
Ugh, ew, ew! Ew!

01:02:53.411 --> 01:02:56.290
Yikes!
Freddy, he's gaining on us.

01:03:11.137 --> 01:03:12.730
Ew, icky.

01:03:15.099 --> 01:03:17.352
He's still right behind us. Huh?

01:03:44.962 --> 01:03:48.057
Heh, I can't watch.
Thanks, Scoob.

01:03:53.596 --> 01:03:54.973
There's no way we can lose him.

01:03:56.516 --> 01:03:58.518
- He's just too fast.
- Look out.

01:04:01.354 --> 01:04:03.732
What are we gonna do?

01:04:05.024 --> 01:04:07.026
Give me that bag.

01:04:52.154 --> 01:04:54.031
Hold it right there.

01:04:54.239 --> 01:04:57.618
Like, heh, that's actually
a pretty good suggestion.

01:05:02.581 --> 01:05:05.209
That is the cleanest sword
I've ever seen.

01:05:05.417 --> 01:05:07.010
Thank you.

01:05:07.210 --> 01:05:09.258
Now I'll take that bag.
Huh?

01:05:16.803 --> 01:05:18.976
The bag, hand it over.

01:05:19.181 --> 01:05:21.149
Why do you want this diamond
so badly, anyway?

01:05:21.349 --> 01:05:25.900
I need it to complete my collection
of cleanliness themed treasures.

01:05:26.104 --> 01:05:29.984
I've already stolen the Ammonia Lisa
and the Sponge of Turin.

01:05:30.192 --> 01:05:31.569
So that was you.

01:05:31.776 --> 01:05:35.030
Uh-huh. But you need three things
to make a collection.

01:05:35.238 --> 01:05:39.084
Three things.
Two is just bookends.

01:05:40.952 --> 01:05:43.831
Now give me the bag.

01:05:47.542 --> 01:05:49.544
- No!
- Dewey.

01:06:02.265 --> 01:06:05.644
Garbage. Unclean.
Unclean.

01:06:05.810 --> 01:06:07.687
Ew, ew, ew!

01:06:07.854 --> 01:06:09.572
But I got the diamond.

01:06:09.773 --> 01:06:13.494
Oh, the soap diamond, gotta find it,
gotta find it, ugh.

01:06:13.652 --> 01:06:15.245
Heh, I've got it.

01:06:17.197 --> 01:06:19.416
Ha, ha. Huh?

01:06:21.535 --> 01:06:26.257
Hmm, yuck, a slobbery dog bone.
Ugh.

01:06:26.414 --> 01:06:28.166
Ooh, too bad.

01:06:38.593 --> 01:06:42.268
And I would have gotten away with it if
it hadn't been for you meddling kids...

01:06:42.472 --> 01:06:45.897
...and your filthy,
germy dog.

01:07:06.621 --> 01:07:10.342
Emma Gale, everyone.
Fantastic.

01:07:10.542 --> 01:07:13.637
Just fantastic, heh.
Hey, look at those numbers.

01:07:13.837 --> 01:07:15.009
Oh, it's going to be close.

01:07:15.171 --> 01:07:17.014
- Ugh.
- Oh, it is going to be close.

01:07:19.968 --> 01:07:22.517
And the voting closes now.

01:07:24.764 --> 01:07:30.021
Fantastic. Fantastic.
Unbelievable. It's a tie.

01:07:30.228 --> 01:07:34.324
Ladies and gentlemen, we're going to
need a tie-breaking encore performance.

01:07:34.524 --> 01:07:37.198
Right here tonight,
right after these messages.

01:07:38.987 --> 01:07:40.113
- This is--
- Fantastic?

01:07:40.322 --> 01:07:42.791
Yes. A tie. Do you have
another piece you can do?

01:07:42.991 --> 01:07:45.289
- Yeah, but Daphne and Fred.
- What about them?

01:07:45.493 --> 01:07:48.042
They aren't here.
They're chasing down another Phantom.

01:07:48.246 --> 01:07:51.125
- Another?
- Apparently this time it's Dewey.

01:07:51.333 --> 01:07:54.052
Heh, always knew there was something
not right about that guy.

01:07:54.252 --> 01:07:57.802
- You. You're the new assistant director.
- Sir, you won't regret this-

01:07:58.006 --> 01:07:59.508
Don't care.
Emma's up after the break.

01:07:59.716 --> 01:08:01.468
We'll just hope Blake and Jones
get back in time. Go.

01:08:04.429 --> 01:08:06.431
- Blake and Jones?
- That's us.

01:08:06.640 --> 01:08:07.892
- We caught--
- Dewey Ottoman.

01:08:08.099 --> 01:08:10.773
Yeah, that Brick guy called,
we know everything.

01:08:10.977 --> 01:08:14.106
- Here's the soap diamond, officer.
- Good work. Now, hop in.

01:08:14.314 --> 01:08:17.193
You tied with the violin girl
so you gotta do a tie-breaker.

01:08:17.399 --> 01:08:19.027
We'll take you back
to the show.

01:08:19.234 --> 01:08:21.953
- Oh, heh, you don't have to do that.
- Yes, I do.

01:08:22.154 --> 01:08:24.408
I got 50 bucks
on you to win.

01:08:28.078 --> 01:08:31.082
So Dewey was the Phantom
who "faded away" in that stairwell.

01:08:31.288 --> 01:08:34.042
- How did he do that?
- I checked the camera in the stairwell.

01:08:34.250 --> 01:08:36.627
He had made a video loop
of the empty stairwell...

01:08:36.836 --> 01:08:38.634
...and spliced it
into the camera feed.

01:08:38.837 --> 01:08:40.636
Of course.
So when he ran in there...

01:08:40.840 --> 01:08:42.638
He activated the loop
with a remote...

01:08:42.841 --> 01:08:45.685
...switching the view on the monitor
to the empty stairwell...

01:08:45.886 --> 01:08:48.935
...and making it look like he disappeared.
- Very clever.

01:08:50.850 --> 01:08:52.944
But, guys, you'll never guess
what I found...

01:08:53.144 --> 01:08:55.818
...when I went through
all the backstage camera footage.

01:08:56.022 --> 01:08:58.366
This is gonna blow
your socks off.

01:09:39.399 --> 01:09:41.777
Fantastic, Emma,
just fantastic.

01:09:43.361 --> 01:09:45.238
And look at those numbers.

01:09:45.447 --> 01:09:49.372
Now it's Blake and
Jones's turn and...

01:09:49.576 --> 01:09:53.421
Well, heh, apparently,
they are not in the building.

01:09:53.621 --> 01:09:57.091
- So it looks like they forfeit their--
You can't bring that dog in here!

01:10:00.587 --> 01:10:02.510
Hold it right there.

01:10:02.714 --> 01:10:06.810
That dog was instrumental in the
apprehension of a dangerous felon.

01:10:06.968 --> 01:10:09.471
Uh, you can bring that
dog in here.

01:10:10.889 --> 01:10:12.891
Come on. We have to make
some arrangements.

01:10:18.646 --> 01:10:21.820
Ladies and gentlemen, Blake and
Jones are here for their tie-breaker.

01:10:22.025 --> 01:10:24.027
- Where were you?
- We caught another Phantom.

01:10:24.235 --> 01:10:25.953
Fantastic, just fantastic.

01:10:26.154 --> 01:10:27.827
- How many does that make now?
- Three.

01:10:28.031 --> 01:10:30.955
- Four if you count the original Phantom.
- Call me Steve.

01:10:32.118 --> 01:10:34.120
Fantastic work.
Fantastic.

01:10:34.329 --> 01:10:36.502
Are you ready
for your tie-breaker performance?

01:10:36.706 --> 01:10:40.677
- We have to do our song again?
- Well, no, you have to do another song, heh.

01:10:40.877 --> 01:10:42.550
Grab your guitar,
you're on.

01:10:42.754 --> 01:10:45.928
Blake and Jones, ladies and gentlemen.
Aren't they fantastic?

01:10:46.132 --> 01:10:48.305
What are we gonna do?
We didn't rehearse anything else.

01:10:48.468 --> 01:10:50.766
I know.
We don't have another song.

01:10:50.970 --> 01:10:53.018
- Wait. Yes, we do.
- What?

01:10:53.223 --> 01:10:56.193
You know that song you wrote?
Well, I wrote some words for it.

01:10:56.392 --> 01:10:59.987
- You did? Why didn't you tell me?
- Just start playing. This will work.

01:11:00.188 --> 01:11:04.034
- It has to.
- Blake and Jones, ladies and gentlemen.

01:11:09.280 --> 01:11:10.577
What is it now?

01:11:10.782 --> 01:11:13.501
You're going to help us
with a little surprise.

01:11:19.457 --> 01:11:23.963
<font color="#00ffff">♫</font> <font color="#00ff00" face="Times New Romance">We've been close a long time</font> <font color="#00ffff">♫</font>

01:11:24.170 --> 01:11:28.926
<font color="#00ffff">♫</font> <font color="#00ff00" face="Times New Romance">As close as friends can be</font> <font color="#00ffff">♫</font>

01:11:29.133 --> 01:11:33.354
<font color="#00ffff">♫</font> <font color="#00ff00" face="Times New Romance">But in my heart's a secret</font> <font color="#00ffff">♫</font>

01:11:34.264 --> 01:11:38.861
<font color="#00ffff">♫</font> <font color="#00ff00" face="Times New Romance">For only you and me</font> <font color="#00ffff">♫</font>

01:11:39.060 --> 01:11:43.691
<font color="#00ffff">♫</font> <font color="#00ff00" face="Times New Romance">I've tried to tell it many times</font> <font color="#00ffff">♫</font>

01:11:43.898 --> 01:11:49.029
<font color="#00ffff">♫</font> <font color="#00ff00" face="Times New Romance">But my nerves got in the way</font> <font color="#00ffff">♫</font>

01:11:49.237 --> 01:11:53.993
<font color="#00ffff">♫</font> <font color="#00ff00" face="Times New Romance">Well, I can't wait another night</font> <font color="#00ffff">♫</font>

01:11:54.200 --> 01:11:58.670
<font color="#00ffff">♫</font> <font color="#00ff00" face="Times New Romance">To say what I must say</font> <font color="#00ffff">♫</font>

01:11:58.871 --> 01:12:01.249
<font color="#00ffff">♫</font> <font color="#00ff00" face="Times New Romance">I love you</font> <font color="#00ffff">♫</font>

01:12:01.456 --> 01:12:03.709
<font color="#00ffff">♫</font> <font color="#00ff00" face="Times New Romance">I love you</font> <font color="#00ffff">♫</font>

01:12:03.917 --> 01:12:08.673
<font color="#00ffff">♫</font> <font color="#00ff00" face="Times New Romance">I love you, yes, I do</font> <font color="#00ffff">♫</font>

01:12:08.881 --> 01:12:13.808
<font color="#00ffff">♫</font> <font color="#00ff00" face="Times New Romance">I love you</font> <font color="#00ffff">♫</font>

01:12:47.294 --> 01:12:50.298
Fantastic! Look at the scoreboard.

01:12:56.553 --> 01:12:57.679
Oh.

01:12:58.430 --> 01:12:59.977
Fred.

01:13:06.730 --> 01:13:11.782
Say, Fred, what bone
will a dog never eat?

01:13:18.867 --> 01:13:20.414
I don't know, Daphne.

01:13:21.662 --> 01:13:23.335
A trombone.

01:13:27.334 --> 01:13:30.679
<i>Say, Fred, what vegetable do you get
when you cross a dog with a rose?</i>

01:13:30.879 --> 01:13:33.758
- I don't know, Daphne.
- A collie-flower.

01:13:36.969 --> 01:13:39.939
- What the heck are they doing?
- They're throwing the contest.

01:13:40.138 --> 01:13:43.108
So Emma can win and her family
can keep their farm.

01:13:43.266 --> 01:13:46.486
Oh, that is so sweet.

01:13:46.687 --> 01:13:49.987
<i>Say, Fred, what did the dog
say to the tree?</i>

01:13:50.190 --> 01:13:53.034
- I don't know, Daphne!
- Bark!

01:14:02.703 --> 01:14:08.255
Well, that was uncomfortable, heh.
All right. The voting closes...

01:14:08.792 --> 01:14:10.385
NOW!

01:14:10.585 --> 01:14:15.432
Fantastic.
The winner is Emma Gale.

01:14:22.139 --> 01:14:25.564
Congratulations, Emma.
Fantastic. Just fantastic.

01:14:25.767 --> 01:14:28.611
And Blake and Jones,
you may not have won...

01:14:28.812 --> 01:14:31.315
...but congratulations on catching
all of the Phantoms.

01:14:31.523 --> 01:14:34.527
- All of them, every last one.
- Not quite all.

01:14:34.735 --> 01:14:37.158
Velma, roll the footage.

01:14:53.920 --> 01:14:56.673
- That's enough, Pimiento.
- Wait, you don't understand.

01:14:56.840 --> 01:14:59.093
I had to do it. The ratings
have been dropping for years.

01:14:59.301 --> 01:15:00.644
I needed the publicity.

01:15:00.844 --> 01:15:04.690
You don't know what it's like, being around
all you talented people all the time...

01:15:04.890 --> 01:15:06.107
...and being me.

01:15:06.308 --> 01:15:10.529
What am I good at? Nothing. All I do
is smile and say "fantastic" a lot.

01:15:10.729 --> 01:15:14.154
- I'm pathetic.
- Come on, Pimiento.

01:15:14.357 --> 01:15:16.109
I would have gotten away with it,
if it hadn't been for--

01:15:16.318 --> 01:15:19.492
Those meddling kids and their nosy dog.
Yeah, yeah, we know.

01:15:19.696 --> 01:15:22.745
- You figure this is the last one?
- I don't know.

01:15:22.949 --> 01:15:27.045
Hey, is anyone else the Phantom?
Show of hands?

01:15:27.245 --> 01:15:29.748
Yeah, looks like we got them all.

01:15:31.374 --> 01:15:34.594
You guys owe me 50 bucks.

01:15:35.545 --> 01:15:37.422
- Uh...
- So, heh...

01:15:38.590 --> 01:15:40.763
Well, a big thank-you
to all our contestants.

01:15:40.967 --> 01:15:45.097
Live from Chicago, this is Steve Trilby
for Talent Star, saying...

01:15:45.305 --> 01:15:48.730
...if you've got the talent,
we've got the star.

01:15:48.934 --> 01:15:51.153
Good night, America.

01:15:53.855 --> 01:15:55.402
This guy's good.

01:16:01.154 --> 01:16:04.203
Scooby-dooby-doo!

01:16:08.055 --> 01:16:14.055
<i><font color="#ff0000" face="Bizarro">Subtitles by "Ghost Who Walks"</font></i>

01:16:18.380 --> 01:16:20.553
We're just gonna run in
and pick up some snacks!

01:16:20.757 --> 01:16:23.931
- Yeah!
- Don't go overboard!

01:16:27.472 --> 01:16:29.099
<i>It was announced today...</i>

01:16:29.266 --> 01:16:31.519
<i>...that Talent Star will be returning
for a tenth season.</i>

01:16:31.726 --> 01:16:37.483
<i>Outgoing host Brick Pimiento will be
replaced by Steve "The Phantom" Trilby.</i>

01:16:37.691 --> 01:16:40.194
- Huh, didn't see that coming.
- Me neither.

01:16:42.779 --> 01:16:44.326
It's driving me crazy!

01:16:44.531 --> 01:16:46.158
- Did he kiss me because he really likes me...
- Oh!

01:16:46.324 --> 01:16:47.496
...or was it all part of the show?

01:16:47.701 --> 01:16:49.499
And does he know that
I really like him?

01:16:49.703 --> 01:16:53.333
How many times to I have to say it?
Just talk to him!

01:16:56.084 --> 01:16:57.677
Huh?

01:16:57.836 --> 01:17:01.136
Guys!
I told you not to go overboard!

01:17:01.339 --> 01:17:04.138
I know, that's why we just
got a couple little things.

01:17:04.342 --> 01:17:06.561
Like what's up, buddy old pal?
ls something bugging you?

01:17:06.761 --> 01:17:08.058
It's driving me crazy.

01:17:08.263 --> 01:17:11.733
Did she kiss me because she really
likes me or was it all part of the show?

01:17:11.933 --> 01:17:13.810
And does she know
that I really like her?

01:17:14.019 --> 01:17:16.067
How many times do
we have to say it?

01:17:16.229 --> 01:17:17.481
Just talk to her!

01:17:22.777 --> 01:17:24.024
- So anyway, I, um,--
- Hey, I was just--

01:17:24.029 --> 01:17:26.157
- Oh, you go ahead.
- Oh, heh, no, you go ahead.

01:17:26.364 --> 01:17:31.245
Okay. Uh, Fred, I just, you know,
wanted to talk to you.

01:17:31.453 --> 01:17:33.922
- Yes?
- Fred, I like--

01:17:34.122 --> 01:17:36.250
Oh, my gosh!
Have you heard about this?

01:17:36.458 --> 01:17:38.506
Some kind of monster's been spotted
at Goose Lake!

01:17:38.710 --> 01:17:40.804
It's just a few miles from here.

01:17:41.004 --> 01:17:42.802
- Wow.
- We should definitely look into that...

01:17:42.964 --> 01:17:45.092
...right away,
it could be something really big.

01:17:45.300 --> 01:17:48.474
All right, everybody.
Let's check out the Goose Lake monster.

01:17:53.225 --> 01:17:56.320
Scooby-dooby-doo!

